result.execSummary:
The defendant Macie L. Huckabay was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 10:10 am [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Donald Hassin presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Macie L. Huckabay in court with Attorney Yelena Olegovna Zarwell. ADA Theresa A Beck appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #1 & #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #2 & #4
Sentencing arguments by ADA Beck; Statements by Mr. Llewellyn Powell; Sentencing arguments by Atty Zarwell

On Counts #1 & #3, THE COURT IMPOSES AND STAYS 90 DAYS JAIL EACH COUNT, CONCURRENT WITHOUT HUBER AND places Defendant on Probation for 18 months, each count, concurrent, with conditions:
--serve 30 days in Jefferson County Jail (On Ct#1), with Huber/Work-Release privileges for any work purpose and for any treatment programs; to commence 3/31/15 by 6:00 pm - Jail sentence may transfer to Wood County as long as electronic monitoring is not utilized 
--AODA Assessment & Follow Through with any recommended treatment
--Not consume any alcoholic beverages or any drugs that aren't prescribed by a doctor
--To pay costs of $486 ($243 each count)
--To pay $400 DNA Surcharge ($200 each count)
--To pay $66 subpoena fees (Count #1)

Days credit for time already served: 4 days
Court orders that if the financial obligations are not paid during course of probation, alternate for failure to pay is 19 days.
Recess: 10:32 am
Jury trial on March 23, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Final status/scheduling conference on March 17, 2015 at 09:00 am.
Pre-trial conference on February 4, 2015 at 08:40 am.
